  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">FOA Zimbabwe Food Crisis Response</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">SUMMARY 
Under this action, which started in November 2019, Plan International Zimbabwe will respond to the drought emergency situation in Zimbabwe, which triggered a food crisis. With a low harvest in 2019 and rising food prices, the availability of food is decreasing, which results in vulnerable households engaging in negative coping mechanisms such as early childhood marriage, withdrawal of children from school and transactional sex. To support vulnerable children and households, the action is focusing on the following key sectors: 1. Sustain education in emergency by ensuring that 85.000 children, especially girls, remain in school, 2. Ensure that child protection mechanisms are in place in assisted communities, focusing on strengthening local structures and identifying protection risks, 3. Strengthening women and girls livelihood capabilities through training and cash-transfer, and 4. Ensure food and nutrition security by meeting the nutrition needs of 25.000 households.</narrative>
  </description>
